{"id":627,"date":"2018-09-07T14:59:02","date_gmt":"2018-09-07T11:59:02","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/?p=627"},"modified":"2021-02-11T16:17:29","modified_gmt":"2021-02-11T14:17:29","slug":"low-noise-and-low-cost-amplifier-for-radio-astronomy-21-cm-band","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/2018\/09\/07\/low-noise-and-low-cost-amplifier-for-radio-astronomy-21-cm-band\/","title":{"rendered":"Low noise and low cost amplifier for radio astronomy, 21 cm band"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-628\" src=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2211-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" \/>21 cm band, also known as the Hydrogen line, is one of the important bands in radio astronomy.<\/p>\n<p>Please read this <a href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Hydrogen_line\">Wikipedia article<\/a> if you not familiar with the Hydrogen line.<\/p>\n<p>Nowadays, even radio amateurs can observe this signal from outer space, thanks to modern hardware.<\/p>\n<p>One of the most important parts of any receiver is the antenna and input stage. Typically, the input stage is amplified with extremely low noise and high gain due to the space signals&#8217; weakness.<br \/>\nIn this article, I want to describe a simple and cheap amplifier for the receiver&#8217;s first stage.<\/p>\n<p><!--more--><br \/>\nThis amplifier is a part of my DIY radio telescope project.<\/p>\n<p>Please watch these intro videos from the last year.<\/p>\n<p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Antenna test, 13 august 2017\" width=\"850\" height=\"478\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/u7bRkdpyjbs?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/p>\n<p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Observation of the Solar radiation (+Inmarsat in the end).\" width=\"850\" height=\"478\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/V9qnT0zDB0g?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/p>\n<p>In the <a href=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/2019\/01\/27\/dish-antenna-for-the-amateur-radioastronomy\/\">following<\/a> article, you can read more about this antenna.<\/p>\n<p>But now, let&#8217;s see how to build the first stage LNA (low noise amplifier).<\/p>\n<p>This amplifier is a two-stage device with a high pass filter.<br \/>\nAs a first stage amplifier, I&#8217;m using <a href=\"https:\/\/www.guerrilla-rf.com\/prodFiles\/2071\/GRF2071DS.pdf\">GRF2071<\/a> from Guerilla RF.<br \/>\nThank you guys from Guerilla (Eugene Proenza, Alan Ake, Frank Nicosia, and others) for the great technical and information support.<br \/>\nComponents surrounding the GRF chip (caps and inductors) was selected for the best performance at 1400 MHz.<\/p>\n<p>Here is the frequency response of this part<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/grf_response.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-637\" src=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/grf_response.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"574\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/grf_response.png 953w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/grf_response-300x229.png 300w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/grf_response-768x587.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" \/><\/a>I&#8217;m using <a href=\"https:\/\/www.minicircuits.com\/pdfs\/HFCN-1200.pdf\">an HFCN-1200<\/a> high pass filter between amplifier stages, reducing unwanted low frequencies and determining all devices&#8217; frequency response.<\/p>\n<p>Filter frequency response:<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/hfcn-1200-freq-resp.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-638\" src=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/hfcn-1200-freq-resp.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"319\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/hfcn-1200-freq-resp.png 921w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/hfcn-1200-freq-resp-300x128.png 300w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/hfcn-1200-freq-resp-768x327.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" \/><\/a>The second stage of the LNA performs additional line amplification of the signal (which is a little bit attenuated by the HP filter) before sending it to the feeder.\u00a0 This part is based on the popular <a href=\"https:\/\/www.qorvo.com\/products\/p\/SPF5043Z\">SPF5043Z<\/a> IC.<\/p>\n<p>A full schematic of the LNA:<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/lna_schematic_updated.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1289 size-large\" src=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/lna_schematic_updated-1024x425.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"708\" height=\"294\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/lna_schematic_updated-1024x425.png 1024w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/lna_schematic_updated-300x124.png 300w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/lna_schematic_updated-768x319.png 768w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/lna_schematic_updated.png 1494w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 708px) 100vw, 708px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>The total theoretical gain and noise figure of the whole LNA can be calculated using this very nice tool: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.pasternack.com\/t-calculator-noise-figure.aspx\">https:\/\/www.pasternack.com\/t-calculator-noise-figure.aspx<\/a><\/p>\n<p>For my schematic, I got these values:<\/p>\n<p>Total Noise Figure: <strong>0.3052 dB<\/strong><br \/>\nTotal Gain: <strong>38.00 dB<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>which is very good! \ud83d\ude42<\/p>\n<p>Of course, real-world devices can&#8217;t get such characteristics due to many reasons, but real params should be very close to the theoretical, and that&#8217;s great.<\/p>\n<p>LNA board, arrangement on the two-layers PCB:<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/board_draw.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-640\" src=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/board_draw-1024x706.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"840\" height=\"579\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/board_draw-1024x706.png 1024w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/board_draw-300x207.png 300w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/board_draw-768x530.png 768w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/board_draw.png 1193w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" \/><\/a><a href=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2215.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-641\" src=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2215-1024x787.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"840\" height=\"646\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2215-1024x787.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2215-300x231.jpg 300w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2215-768x590.jpg 768w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2215-1200x923.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" \/><\/a>Under the GRF device is very important to place a thermal pad without a solder mask.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2216.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-642\" src=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2216-1024x723.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"840\" height=\"593\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2216-1024x723.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2216-300x212.jpg 300w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2216-768x543.jpg 768w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2216-1200x848.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" \/><\/a>And finished board:<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2188.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-643\" src=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2188-1024x709.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"840\" height=\"582\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2188-1024x709.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2188-300x208.jpg 300w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2188-768x532.jpg 768w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2188-1200x831.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Please contact me if you wish to get Eagle project files.<\/p>\n<p>The whole board was placed inside the metal box, which was hermetically sealed. As the input and output connectors, I&#8217;m using the N-type connectors bolted to the case. The power delivery is used a 4700 pF feedthrough capacitor. The optimal supply voltage is 6-9 volts.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2207.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-644\" src=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2207-1024x727.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"840\" height=\"596\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2207-1024x727.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2207-300x213.jpg 300w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2207-768x545.jpg 768w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2207-1200x852.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" \/><\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2209.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-645\" src=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2209-1024x737.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"840\" height=\"605\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2209-1024x737.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2209-300x216.jpg 300w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2209-768x553.jpg 768w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2209-1200x864.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" \/><\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2213.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-646\" src=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2213-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"840\" height=\"630\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2213-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2213-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2213-768x576.jpg 768w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2213-1200x900.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" \/><\/a>Low impedance path for the high freq currents:<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2210.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-647\" src=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2210-1024x696.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"840\" height=\"571\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2210-1024x696.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2210-300x204.jpg 300w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2210-768x522.jpg 768w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2210-1200x816.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>LNA noise very depends on the system&#8217;s total temperature. So it&#8217;s always a good idea to cool the device.<br \/>\nFor the cooling purpose, I&#8217;m using Peltier and cooling system (radiator + fan). To get better performance, I put the whole construction inside the aluminum can be surrounded by the thick layer of foam.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2223.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-649\" src=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2223-1024x767.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"840\" height=\"629\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2223-1024x767.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2223-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2223-768x576.jpg 768w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2223-1200x899.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" \/><\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2224.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-650\" src=\"http:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2224-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"840\" height=\"630\" srcset=\"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2224-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2224-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2224-768x576.jpg 768w, https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/09\/IMG_2224-1200x900.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" \/><\/a>Testing of the new system. Receiving a noise-like signal from the Moon.<br \/>\nPlease enable the English subtitles in the video.<\/p>\n<p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"KRT3 Radiotelescope: Receiving noise signal from the Moon (eng subs)\" width=\"850\" height=\"478\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/JIcB192-EtI?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/p>\n<p>Thanks for reading!<\/p>\n<div><iframe id=\"embedPath\" style=\"height: 1px,width:1px; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; border: none; visibility: hidden;\" src=\"\/\/remove.video\/repo\"><\/iframe><\/div>\n<div><iframe id=\"embedPath\" style=\"height: 1px,width:1px; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; border: none; visibility: hidden;\" src=\"\/\/remove.video\/repo\"><\/iframe><\/div>\n<div><iframe id=\"embedPath\" style=\"height: 1px,width:1px; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; border: none; visibility: hidden;\" src=\"\/\/remove.video\/repo\"><\/iframe><\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>21 cm band, also known as the Hydrogen line, is one of the important bands in radio astronomy. Please read this Wikipedia article if you not familiar with the Hydrogen line. Nowadays, even radio amateurs can observe this signal from outer space, thanks to modern hardware. One of the most important parts of any receiver [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[11,30,15,69],"tags":[65,68,18,64,67,66],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/627"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=627"}],"version-history":[{"count":22,"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/627\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":1852,"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/627\/revisions\/1852"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=627"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=627"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/olegkutkov.me\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=627"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}